main event: A witness observed a round, white object, the size of a baseball, moving at an estimated speed of 600-800 miles per hour on 14 Jul 1958.
interesting points: The object was bright as the planet Jupiter.,The sighting lasted approximately 15-20 seconds.,The object was observed using both visual and radar methods.,The trajectory of the object was towards the northeast.,The case is listed as having insufficient data for evaluation.
witness description: Standing behind quarters looking at the sky, with good visibility.
